data.enText: used to say what normally happens in a particular situation
In the ordinary way, she's not a nervous person.
data.chText: 一般而言，她是个不爱紧张的人。

data.enText: I'm looking for something a little more out of the ordinary.
data.chText: 我正在找些稍不寻常的东西。

tr: (heraldry) any of several conventional figures used on shields
an early bicycle with a very large front wheel and small back wheel
a judge of a probate court
a clergyman appointed to prepare condemned prisoners for death
the expected or commonplace condition or situation
lacking special distinction, rank, or status
example: the ordinary (or common) man in the street

tr: not exceptional in any way especially in quality or ability or size or degree

data.enText: not unusual or different in any way
data.chText: 普通的；平常的；一般的；平凡的

data.enText: in the ordinary course of events
ordinary people like you and me
having no unusual or interesting features
used to say what normally happens in a particular situation
In the ordinary way, she's not a nervous person.
data.chText: 一般而言，她是个不爱紧张的人。

data.enText: I'm looking for something a little more out of the ordinary.
data.chText: 我正在找些稍不寻常的东西。

ex.enText: It is a popular misunderstanding that the higher the price is, the better the product will be.
ex.chText: 一种普遍的错误观念认为：东西越贵，质量就会越好。

ex.enText: Was popular opinion divided on the real-name train ticket system?
ex.chText: 对于实名购买火车票制度，民众意见有分歧吗？

synonyms.bx: 指想法、信仰等为大部分人所持有并接受的，只作定语。

ex.enText: Insomnia is fairly common among adults.
ex.chText: 成年人失眠是常有的事。

ex.enText: It is common for children to be afraid of sleeping alone.
ex.chText: 小孩子不敢一个人睡觉是很常见的。

synonyms.bx: 指经常在多人身上或多个地方发生的。

ex.enText: This movie is about ordinary people.
ex.chText: 这部电影是关于普通人的。

ex.enText: Physical exercise should be part of ordinary life.
ex.chText: 体育锻炼理应是日常生活的一部分。

ex.enText: I recommend this novel because it is written in ordinary language.
ex.chText: 我推荐这本小说是因为它是用平凡的语言写成的。

synonyms.bx: 指平常的，没有不同或特别之处的。

ex.enText: House price is a topic of universal interest.
ex.chText: 房价是人们普遍关注的一个问题。

synonyms.bx: 指包括某一群体中的每个人在内的，无一例外。

synonym.guide: 导航词义：普通的，普遍的

example.ex: I strongly suspect that most ordinary people would agree with me...
example.tran: 我坚定地认为绝大部分老百姓会赞同我的观点。

example.ex: It has 25 calories less than ordinary ice cream...
example.tran: 它所含热量比普通的冰激凌少了25卡路里。

example.ex: It was just an ordinary weekend for us.
example.tran: 对我们来说，这只是一个平常的周末。

value.def: Ordinary people or things are normal and not special or different in any way.
value.tran: 平常的；普通的；一般的；平凡的

example.ex: I'm just a very ordinary, boring normal guy...
example.tran: 我只是一个颇为平庸无趣的普通人。

example.ex: Your life since then must have seemed very ordinary.
example.tran: 你的生活从那时起一定非常平淡无奇。

example.ex: ...very ordinary, if very well made, drinking glasses, lamps and tableware.
example.tran: 制作精良但毫无特色的酒杯、灯具和餐具

value.def: If you describe someone or something as ordinary, you mean they are not special or interesting in any way and may be rather dull.

example.ex: The boy's knowledge was out of the ordinary...
example.tran: 这个男孩懂得的知识非比寻常。

example.ex: I've noticed nothing out of the ordinary.
example.tran: 我没注意到什么特别之处。

value.def: Something that is out of the ordinary is unusual or different.
value.tran: 不寻常的；非凡的；特殊的

trans: 与众不同；不寻常的；非凡的；特殊的
